# Force LF line endings for Simple language source files.
# CRLF breaks the indentation-sensitive parser.
*.spl text eol=lf
*.shs text eol=lf
*.sdn text eol=lf

# SDN database files — prevent text merge, keep current branch copy on conflict.
#
# Why:
#   SDN files are machine-managed databases (BugDB, FeatureDB, TestDB, RequirementDB).
#   The database API uses atomic file-locking writes. Two-way text merge would corrupt
#   the tabular format (|col1, col2| rows) and break auto-increment IDs.
#   After merge, regenerate with: bin/simple bug-gen, bin/simple test, etc.
#
# How it works:
#   merge=ours keeps the current branch version when both sides changed the file.
#   If only one side changed, git fast-forwards normally (driver is not invoked).
#   Requires one-time setup: git config merge.ours.driver true
#
# jj note:
#   jj does NOT support .gitattributes merge drivers (issues #5264, #8071).
#   SDN conflicts during jj rebase must be resolved manually via: jj resolve
#   Then regenerate the database files.
#
*.sdn merge=ours
